==English==
===Noun===
'''juju'''

# A [[fetish]] or [[charm]] believed by West Africans to have [[magical]] or [[supernatural]] powers.
# The magical or supernatural power of such a charm. 
# A type of music popular in [[Nigeria]].

====Derived terms====
* [[jujuism]]

==Finnish==
===Noun===
'''juju'''
# A [[catch]], a problem, a snag, especially in a deal or negotiation; a [[hitch]]
#:''It sounds like a great idea, but what's the '''catch'''? '''In Finnish:''' Kuulostaa hyvältä idealta, mutta mikä on homman '''juju'''?''

==Bengali==
===Noun===
'''juju'''
# A fictional [[bogeyman]], commonly used to scare young children. Conceptually similar to the Western [[Sandman]].
#:''Go to sleep, or the '''bogeyman''' will come for you. '''In Bengali:''' ঘুমিয়ে পর। নাহলে '''যুযু''' আশবে।

